<subSubSection id="C368652E935B8E06F2AAFEFDFCC2FE1A" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935B8E06F2AAFEFDFCC2FE1A" blockId="2.[151,1436,367,681]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF8935B8E06F2AAFEFDFCDEFE1A" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147340" collectorName="L. Bedel &amp; J. Serrano" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="holotype">
The specimen here recognized as the 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935B8E06F007FEFDFD4DFE42" box="[570,668,367,393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">holotype</typeStatus>
is a female bearing the labels “mentun subdentatum/calcare trifido”, “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935B8E06F299FE01FEF9FE66" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[164,296,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F299FE01FEF9FE66" box="[164,296,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mihi in Gal. mer. Perpignan”, “ex-Museo Chaudoir”, “ 
<collectorName id="26875373935B8E06F1AAFE01FC28FE66" box="[919,1017,403,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">L. Bedel</collectorName>
vidit 1897” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935B8E06F6FCFE01FAFDFE66" box="[1217,1324,403,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935B8E06F76EFE01FDCDFE1A" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F76EFE01FE51FE1A" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Anisodactylus intermedius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F3BAFE25FDCDFE1A" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[391,540,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="26875373935B8E06F0B2FE25FCD4FE1A" box="[655,773,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E935B8E06F2FAFE49FF31FD62" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935B8E06F2FAFE49FF31FDA9" blockId="2.[151,1436,367,681]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">
The species is currently included in the monotypic subgenus 
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F1A7FE49FB81FE3E" box="[922,1104,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Pseudodichirius</emphasis>
Lutshnik, 1921b (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F717FE49FEE5FDD2" author="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W." pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="1854" refId="ref11592" refString="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (2017 a) Subtribe Anisodactylina Lacordaire, 1854. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 503 - 509." type="book chapter" year="2017">Kataev &amp; Wrase, 2017a</bibRefCitation>
), according to the trifid apical spur of protibial, pilosity of elytra, valvifers and other characters. Morphological characters of the 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935B8E06F3EFFDB1FDE5FDF6" box="[466,564,547,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">holotype</typeStatus>
are correctly described in current classifications (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F6A8FDB1FAE0FDF6" author="Jeannel, R." box="[1173,1329,547,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="572 - 1173" refId="ref11231" refString="Jeannel, R. (1942) Coleopteres carabiques. Deuxieme partie. Faune de France 40. Librairie de la Faculte des Sciences, Paris, pp. 572 - 1173." type="book chapter" year="1942">Jeannel, 1942</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F700FDB1FF02FDA9" author="Noonan, G. R." pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="1 - 210" refId="ref11934" refString="Noonan, G. R. (1996) Classification, cladistics, and natural history of species of the subgenus Anisodactylus Dejean (Insecta: Coleoptera: Carabidae: Harpalini: Anisodactylus). Milwaukee Public Museum, Contributions in Biology and Geology, No. 89, I - III + 1 - 210." type="book chapter" year="1996">Noonan, 1996</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935B8E06F2FAFDF9FF31FD62" blockId="2.[151,1436,367,681]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">
The species is distributed from the northern side of the Mediterranean to 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935B8E06F1D1FDF9FBBBFD4E" box="[1004,1130,619,645]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935B8E06F6A3FDF9FAE8FD4E" box="[1182,1337,619,645]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F77BFDF9FF05FD62" author="Kataev, B. M." pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="721 - 736" refId="ref11345" refString="Kataev, B. M. (2002) Taxonomic, faunistic and nomenclatural notes on certain Palaearctic and Oriental Harpalini (Coleoptera, Carabidae). Linzer Biologische Beitrage, 34, 721 - 736." type="journal article" year="2002">Kataev, 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
